Avi Rubin (rubin@faline.bellcore.com) writes:

> Is there a way to use PGP to compute the MD-5 digest of an
> arbitrary file without involving any keys or signatures? If
> not, has anyone implemented a user interface with the following
> functionality?

> Enter file name: my.file
> The MD-5 hash of this data is: x87 A6 B2 C9 32 2D etc.

Why do you need this functionality as a part of PGP? There are plenty
of stand-alone MD5 implementations around, which produce such output.

